div.style: color: rgb(255, 255, 255) !important; display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p: JOB INPUT: Brand + Model + Category

div.style: color: rgb(224, 231, 255) !important; display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
PHASE 00
Harness + Config
Loads field rules, schema,
component DB. Creates run
directory + NDJSON stream.
Emits run_context event.

div.style: color: rgb(255, 255, 255) !important; display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
LLM: Brand Resolver
Role: triage
Given a brand name and category,
finds the official website domain.
Sends: brand + category
Gets back: official domain, aliases,
support subdomain
Example: Razer razer.com
Cached in SQLite permanently

div.style: color: rgb(236, 253, 245) !important; display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
Source Strategy
GUI-editable SQLite table
of known review sites.
host + tier + priority +
discovery method per site.
Replaces hardcoded adapters.

div.style: color: rgb(243, 232, 255) !important; display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
PHASE 01: NeedSet
Scores every field by how
badly it needs more evidence.
Tiered identity caps:
full 0.70 provisional 0.500.70
abort <0.50. Freshness decay
via exponential half-life.
need = missing conf tier refs

div.style: color: rgb(255, 255, 255) !important; display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
PHASE 02: Search Planner
Role: plan up to 4 passes
Builds structured SearchProfile
with target_fields per query.
Sends: product identity, critical fields,
missing fields, existing queries
Gets back: 5-12 search queries each
tagged with target_fields so the
convergence loop knows which fields
each query is trying to fill

div.style: color: rgb(255, 255, 255) !important; display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
PHASE 09: CONVERGENCE ROUND N
NeedSet drives each round
7 stop conditions: complete max_rounds
no_progress budget low_quality
identity_gate_stuck escalation_exhausted

div.style: color: rgb(243, 232, 255) !important; display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
PHASE 03
Search Providers
Google + SearXNG + DDG
Multi-provider fan-out
Results deduplicated
across providers

div.style: color: rgb(255, 255, 255) !important; display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
LLM: URL Predictor
Role: triage
Given the product and known review
sites from Source Strategy, predicts
the most likely URL per site.
Skips search entirely for known hosts.
Sends: product + known source hosts
Gets back: predicted URLs per source
with confidence score and tier
Each URL HEAD-checked: 200=fetch,
404=skip. Saves search budget.

div.style: color: rgb(254, 243, 199) !important; display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
LLM: SERP Reranker
Role: plan highest-impact LLM call
After search results come back, sends
ALL results to the LLM in one call to
filter the useful from the junk.
Sends: identity lock, missing fields,
full result list with url + title +
snippet + deterministic score
Gets back: keep or drop per URL with
reason tag like manufacturer_official,
lab_review, wrong_product, irrelevant
Keeps top 8-15 of 50-100 results.
One $0.001 call saves 80% of fetches.

div.style: color: rgb(255, 255, 255) !important; display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
LLM: Domain Safety Gate
Role: triage
Before fetching any unknown domain,
classifies it for safety in batches.
Sends: batch of up to 30 domains
Gets back: classification per domain:
manufacturer, lab_review, retail,
forum, adult_content, malware, etc.
adult + malware permanently blocked.
Cached in SQLite domain_classifications.

div.style: color: rgb(243, 232, 255) !important; display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
PHASE 04
URL Health + Frontier
Tracks per-URL status:
200/403/404/410/timeout
Cooldown timers per host
Repair signals refetch queue
Host budget scoring

div.style: color: rgb(224, 231, 255) !important; display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
PHASE 05: Fetch + Parse
Bounded concurrent scheduler:
HostPacer enforces per-host delay
Fallback ladder on error:
Crawlee Playwright HTTP
(403 timeout 5xx network)
PHASE 11 worker lanes:
WORKERS_SEARCH/FETCH/PARSE/LLM
Parsing: static HTML, dynamic JS,
PDF, scanned OCR, article, tables,
structured metadata, visual capture

div.style: color: rgb(243, 232, 255) !important; display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
PHASE 06: Evidence
06A: FTS5 SQLite index
Stable snippet_ids from
content_hash + parser version
Dedupe: new / reused / updated
Chunks + facts indexed
06B: Refetch Queue
Durable automation queue
Worker loop + TTL policy
Domain staleness refresh
Repair signal consumption

div.style: color: rgb(243, 232, 255) !important; display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
PHASE 07: Tier Retrieval
FTS-powered evidence ranking
per field using tier_preference.
Tiered identity gate:
0.70 full extraction
0.500.70 provisional (tagged)
<0.50 abort all fields.
Miss diagnostics per field:
pool_empty no_anchor 
tier_deficit identity_mismatch
Prime sources selected per field.

div.style: color: rgb(255, 255, 255) !important; display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
PHASE 08: Extraction
Role: extract + plan core engine
ExtractionContextAssembler builds
per-field context from prime sources.
Visual asset refs for ambiguous fields.
Sends: evidence text, field contracts
with type/unit/enum/shape, product
identity, extraction context matrix,
golden examples, component DB refs
Gets back: field candidates each with
value, confidence 0-1, direct quote,
evidence refs, and any conflicts found
Batched by field group + difficulty.
Easy fields: fast model
Hard fields: reasoning model

div.style: color: rgb(255, 255, 255) !important; display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
LLM: Component Validator
Role: validate
When extraction finds a component
name that does not exactly match
the component database, asks the
LLM to decide: is this the same
part under a different name, a
genuinely new component, or junk?
Sends: raw name vs DB candidate
properties + variance policies
Gets back: same_component or
new_component or reject, plus
confidence, reasoning, and a
suggested alias if same.
Example: PAW3950 = PixArt PMW3950

div.style: color: rgb(243, 232, 255) !important; display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
CONSENSUS ENGINE
Multi-source agreement
scoring. Each candidate
weighted by extraction
method and evidence tier.
Tier-1 mfr outweighs Tier-3
retail. All weights GUI-tunable.
Selection policy and list union
reducers resolve conflicts
across sources.

div.style: color: rgb(255, 255, 255) !important; display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
LLM: Field Validation
Role: validate final accuracy gate
After consensus scoring, some fields
remain uncertain with low confidence
or conflicting values. Sends those
fields to the LLM as a final judge.
Sends: uncertain fields with current
values, full provenance per field
showing which URLs at which tiers
using which methods produced what
Gets back: accept, reject, or unknown
per field with reason, confidence,
and evidence refs. Unknown fields
also get next_best_queries hints.

div.style: display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
STOP?
complete max_rounds
no_progress budget
low_quality identity_stuck
escalation_exhausted

div.style: color: rgb(255, 255, 255) !important; display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
LLM: Escalation Planner
Role: plan reasoning model
When fields remain missing after a
round, generates targeted surgical
re-queries specifically aimed at
those gaps. Avoids repeating query
patterns that already failed.
Sends: still-missing fields, product
identity, all previously-tried queries
Gets back: new queries per field with
target_fields + expected source type
like datasheet, teardown, tech DB.
Deduped against all prior queries.
Feeds directly into next round.

div.style: color: rgb(254, 242, 242) !important; display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
PHASE 10
Learning Gates
5 acceptance gates:
confidence 0.85
field status = accepted
refs min_refs
tier 1 or 2 in history
component review accepted

div.style: color: rgb(254, 242, 242) !important; display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
Learning Stores
Four stores with decay:
component_lexicon (90d)
field_anchors (60d)
url_memory (120d)
domain_field_yield
Propose via suggestions,
never auto-mutate rules.
Product B benefits from
Product A learned anchors.

div.style: color: rgb(255, 255, 255) !important; display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
LLM: Summary Writer
Role: write
After the pipeline finishes, asks the
LLM to write a concise markdown
summary of the harvested results.
Sends: validated field values, quality
scores, completeness percentage,
provenance data per field
Gets back: factual markdown summary
mentioning confirmed values, source
counts, and unknowns. No opinions
or inferences only verified data.

div.style: color: rgb(243, 232, 255) !important; display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
OUTPUT
Spec JSON + NDJSON events
Provenance trail per field
Evidence refs + confidence
Component review data
Export to database

div.style: color: rgb(254, 242, 242) !important; display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
PHASE 12
Batch Queue
Durable SQLite state machine:
queued / running / completed
failed / skipped / stopped
Resumable across restarts
Batch lifecycle APIs
Next product dispatch

div.style: color: rgb(255, 255, 255) !important; display: table-cell; white-space: nowrap; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center;

span.p: BATCH COMPLETE
